# Tailwind CSS Styling

Use Tailwind CSS utility classes for all styling. Avoid writing custom CSS or `<style>` blocks.

- Prefer Tailwind utility classes directly in templates over `<style scoped>` blocks.
- Use Tailwind's design tokens (spacing, colors, typography) for visual consistency.
- When a combination of utilities is reused, extract it with `@apply` in a shared CSS layer or create a component.
- Never use inline `style` attributes for layout, spacing, or colors.

```vue
<!-- ❌ BAD -->
<template>
  <div style="padding: 16px; background: #1a1d27;">
    <button class="custom-btn">Click</button>
  </div>
</template>
<style scoped>
.custom-btn { padding: 8px 16px; border-radius: 8px; background: #6366f1; color: white; }
</style>

<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<template>
  <div class="p-4 bg-gray-900">
    <button class="px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-indigo-500 text-white hover:bg-indigo-400 transition-colors">
      Click
    </button>
  </div>
</template>
```
